ref-5-3-8                    Xerox Quintus Prolog Reference Manual                         Section 5-3-8: nofileerrorsnofileerrors/0 resets the 'fileerrors' flag, so that the built-in predicateswhich open files simply fail, instead of producing an error message and thencalling abort/0, if the specified file cannot be opened.The 'fileerrors' flag is only enabled by an explicit call to fileerrors/0, orvia prolog_flag/[2,3] which can also be used to obtain the current value of the'fileerrors' flag.  See {manual(ref-18-3)}, for more information on the'fileerrors' flag.nofileerrors/0 has no associated error conditions.